   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The Dark Twins are the most powerful core magi in the game. They take up two slots, but the sacrifice is well worth it. They start out with entomb (thats already worth it), ANY one core creature,(Darkbreed Hyrens are always promising), and any one core spell. If you&#39;re wondering why one magi for two slots is good, it&#39;s mostly because the twins can choose to go first every game without a die roll. And, if they go first, they get to draw seven starting cards instead of five.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
If you get to morag, be completely aggressive with him. It&#39;s basically your only chance. You getting to morag is not likely. <br>
<br><br>
This deck excels at creature control and at causing suprime chaos.<br>
<br><br>
First of all, the creatures in this deck are pure offensive.  For example, Wudge. Each time your opponent plays a creature, Wudge gains energy.  If you where playing a swarm deck, you would have a big Wudgie!  <br>
<br><br>
One really good combo would be Koil and Turn.  For those of you who dont know, when you play a Koil, it removes one energy from any one creature. Then you could bust out a turn. Not only does Koil help Turn things, but it also is a cheaper Dream Rift.<br>
<br><br>
Vrill is also a great card.You should only play it if you have a huge army and a shadow bones cause once that creature is played, it will be the main target.<br>
<br><br>
Second of all, This deck contains some havoc reaping spells.  Use the first Entomb on the shockwave in this deck. Use the second Entomb on any other spell that you want.Blight and turn are also a good combo.<br>
<br><br>
<br><br>
Enjoy <br>
<br>
